content:
A Data Mapper Post Action invokes a Data Mapper Load to write data to one or more Salesforce objects.

If the Data Mapper Load doesn't already exist, you can create it by clicking Create New Data Mapper immediately after dragging the Data Mapper Post Action into the OmniScript structure panel.

Drag the Data Mapper Post Action into the OmniScript's structure panel.
To select the Data Mapper Load to be called, click in the Data Mapper Interface field and select from the list. You can type in the field to filter the list.
Use the Send Transformations properties to trim or rename the input JSON so it has the structure the Data Mapper Load expects.
